parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while in motion, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while in motion
warning lights appear on the dashboard
loss of headlights
tail lights
or emergency flashers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the battery to drain, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery warning light appears on the dashboard
the vehicle loses power
the headlights or other electrical systems malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery warning light appears on the dashboard
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the headlights or other electrical systems malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine fire can cause serious damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants or other road users.
symptoms: The engine catches fire
smoke appears from the hood
the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power lift gate can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to accidents if the gate fails to close properly.
symptoms: The power lift gate fails to close
beeping noises occur
the gate must be closed manually.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver seat motor can cause discomfort and potentially lead to accidents if the driver is distracted or unable to adjust their seat properly.
symptoms: The driver seat motor fails to work properly
the seat does not adjust to the correct height
the seat base does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ability to remove the ignition key while the vehicle is in gear can cause accidents or rollaway incidents.
symptoms: The ignition key can be removed while the vehicle is in gear
the vehicle can roll away or move unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel is hard to turn
the steering wheel is tight
the power steering reservoir is empty
fluid is leaking from the steering rack and pinion
sparks are coming from the steering wheel
abnormal cranking sound is heard from the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack and pinion can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Fluid is leaking from the steering rack and pinion
the power steering reservoir is empty
the steering wheel is hard to turn
the steering wheel is tight.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the control arm can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's steering locks up
the vehicle crashes into a road divider
the control arm is visibly bent.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and come to an unexpected stop, increasing the risk of accidents, especially in high-traffic areas.
symptoms: The engine suddenly stops running
often without warning
while driving; the vehicle may be able to be restarted by turning the ignition switch off and back on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, increased emissions, and potentially cause engine failure, which can result in costly repairs and pose a safety risk.
symptoms: The engine consumes a lot of oil
requiring frequent oil additions between recommended oil change intervals; the vehicle may leave oil spots or stains on the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical interference from the vehicle's Bluetooth system or other sources may cause the engine to stall or malfunction, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stops running suddenly
especially when the vehicle is near railroad crossings or other areas with potential electrical interference; the issue may be resolved by turning off the Bluetooth system.
